710205f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 49th Street (West)
710205f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from West 49th (left), to 50th
(right) Street's, showing the Eighth Avenue Railroad car-barn
prior to demolition and the site cleared for the new Madison
Square Garden. Note the billboards on the 30th Street side
announcing the Circus at the still employed old Garden on
Madison Avenue and 26th Street.
Prior to 1926
